ve In, Julián Daniel Gutiérrez-Albilla explores how Almodóvar’s cinema mourns and witnesses the traces of trauma, drawing on theoretical approaches from trauma studies, psychoanalysis, philosophy, film studies and visual studies to suggest that his work proposes an ethical model based on our compassionate relations to others, and envisions a world co-inhabited by plurality and difference.Key featuresExplores how Pedro Almodóvar engages with the traumatic pastIncludes close readings of Almodóvar’s films from the 1990s and 2000sDraws on theoretical approaches from trauma studies, psychoanalysis, philosophy, film studies and visual studies  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 0aMotion pictureszSpainxHistory and criticism. 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Direction & Production.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311078140340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474400114423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474400114/original  a978-3-11-078140-3  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK